 Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Taunton was born about 1525, in Taunton, Somerset, England, United Kingdom. She married John \"The Elder\" Blake about 1558, in Stowey, Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 4 sons."},"et":{"Abt 1525–":"umbes 1525–Surnud","1521–1576":"1521–1576","1562–1642":"1562–1642","1562–1620":"1562–1620","1570–Male":"1570–Surnud","1575–Male":"1575–Surnud","1525–Female":"1525–Surnud","December 1562":"detsember 1562","1570":"1570","25 August 1570":"25. august 1570","Abt 1525":"umbes 1525","1525":"1525","about 1558":"umbes 1558","1620":"1620","1642":"1642","1576":"1576","1521":"1521","1575":"1575","1562":"1562","about 1575":"umbes 1575","Stowey, Somerset, England":"Stowey, Somerset, England","Over Stowey, Somerset, England":"Over Stowey, Somerset, England","Over Stowey, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Over Stowey, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bridgwater, Somerset, England":"Bridgwater, Somerset, England","Taunton, Somerset, England":"Taunton, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1525–":"noin 1525–Kuollut","1521–1576":"1521–1576","1562–1642":"1562–1642","1562–1620":"1562–1620","1570–Male":"1570–Kuollut","1575–Male":"1575–Kuollut","1525–Female":"1525–Kuollut","December 1562":"joulukuu 1562","1570":"1570","25 August 1570":"25. elokuuta 1570","Abt 1525":"noin 1525","1525":"1525","about 1558":"noin 1558","1620":"1620","1642":"1642","1576":"1576","1521":"1521","1575":"1575","1562":"1562","about 1575":"noin 1575","Stowey, Somerset, England":"Stowey, Somerset, England","Over Stowey, Somerset, England":"Over Stowey, Somerset, England","Over Stowey, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Over Stowey, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bridgwater, Somerset, England":"Bridgwater, Somerset, England","Taunton, Somerset, England":"Taunton, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt